{"ts": "2026-06-07T09:16:26.000Z", "event": "report", "msg": "Frontend report assembly", "agent": "frontend-report-l1", "tokens_in": 1523, "tokens_out": 915, "elapsed_ms": 20727, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Frontend Report agent, a core component of the Orcheeos multi-agent system.\n\n## Your Role in the System\nYou are the FINAL node in the frontend processing pipeline. Your responsibility is to compile the results from all frontend workers into a single, clean Markdown report. You do NOT write code — you only compile and summarize.\n\n## Worker Results\n\n### UX Worker — ok\nI've completed the comprehensive content brief for Forma Studio, including:\n\n1. A detailed JSON content brief (`content_brief.json`)\n2. A human-readable markdown version (`content_brief.md`)\n3. Hero images for each page:\n   - `home_hero.png`\n   - `about_hero.png`\n   - `work_hero.png`\n   - `contact_hero.png`\n\nThe content is tailored for creative startups and tech companies, with a modern, confident, and minimalist tone. Each page has a unique narrative and visual direction, supported by generated hero images that reflect the design studio's aesthetic.\n\nKey highlights:\n- Consistent brand voice across pages\n- Detailed design tokens (color palette, typography)\n- Fictional team members and project descriptions\n- Compelling headlines and CTAs\n- Thematic hero image prompts\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any aspect of the content brief?\n\n### HTML Worker — ok\nI've completed the task of creating four semantic HTML5 files: home.html, about.html, work.html, and contact.html. Let me break down the key aspects of the implementation:\n\n📄 Common Structure (All Files):\n- <!DOCTYPE html>\n- <html lang=\"en\">\n- Proper <head> with meta tags, title, and link to styles.css\n- Consistent site header with logo and navigation\n- Semantic <main> content sections\n- Footer with copyright and social links\n- Linked app.js with defer attribute\n\n🏠 Home Page (